"async and await make promises easier to write"

async makes a

function
return a Promise

await makes a

function wait
for a Promise


The keyword async before a

function makes the

function
return a promise:

    Example
async function myFunction() {
    return "Hello";
}
Is the same as:

    function myFunction() {
        return Promise.resolve("Hello");
    }


Await Syntax
The await keyword can only be used inside an async function.

The await keyword makes the
function pause the execution and wait
for a resolved promise before it continues: